## 5. MANDATORY — Salesforce 24-hour security-incident report

<!-- guidance: This section is the reviewer's highest-signal read in this
document and is NON-NEGOTIABLE per baseline post-incident-reporting-24h. Do NOT
soften it: a confirmed incident affecting Salesforce customer data MUST be
reported to Salesforce within 24 hours of confirmation. The owner fills the
report-owner and the internal trigger; the duty, window, and destination are
fixed by the baseline. -->

**Duty (fixed — baseline `post-incident-reporting-24h`).** Upon a **confirmed**
security incident affecting Salesforce customer data — including a vulnerability
reasonably expected to result in unauthorized disclosure or access — notify
Salesforce security **without undue delay and within 24 hours** of confirmation,
to **{{SALESFORCE_SECURITY_CONTACT}}**, with: a technical account of the
incident, an impact analysis (which customers / data are affected), the
remediation status, and a response contact.

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| Trigger (internal) | {{REPORT_TRIGGER}} <!-- owner: the §3 severity row(s) that start the clock --> |
| Window | **24 hours from confirmation** (fixed) |
| Destination | {{SALESFORCE_SECURITY_CONTACT}} (fixed — confirm current per CA/ECA) |
| Report owner | {{REPORT_OWNER}} <!-- owner: the named person who sends it --> |
| Recurring tracking | This obligation persists post-approval; watched by `/sf-security-review-toolkit:stay-listed`. |

> The 24-hour window and the destination are pinned from the baseline; the
> owner attests they remain current against the partner program (CA/ECA) and
> their Partner Account Manager. The baseline notes the window itself has not
> been re-verified against a current primary source — confirm before relying.

